\par\par \b \uc2 Business giants raise concern over rupiah  \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post/Jakarta  \par \uc2 672 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 December 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 1\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 The volatile rupiah exchange rate against the greenback remains a great concern for foreign investors operating in Indonesia, as any \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could cause unnecessary downturns in their businesses.  \par \par \uc2 In a rare closed-door meeting with President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono on Friday, 22 top executives of major foreign companies or their local arms expressed their concern over the issue and were seeking direct input on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition from the president.  \par \par \uc2 The Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) vice chairman for international \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cooperation, John A. Prasetio, the moderator in the meeting, told The Jakarta Post of the deep concerns of businesspeople and the need to create a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  that ensured the stability of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar.  \par \par \uc2 "The businessmen have expressed their optimism over investment opportunities in Indonesia. However, they are still concerned over \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the rupiah exchange, which they say was 'chronically weak'," he said.  \par \par \uc2 "They fear that unless there are immediate and substantial changes in \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , a sharp depreciation in the rupiah will happen again in the future, thus, creating \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the operation of their businesses here," he added.  \par \par \uc2 The rupiah started to nosedive in August when it slumped to a four-year low to around Rp 11,000 against the dollar, despite optimism from the Cabinet's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team at that time that the rupiah was going to stay at around Rp 9,500.  \par \par \uc2 The slump was triggered by the soaring global oil prices -- which passed the US$70 per barrel mark on Aug. 30 -- that eventually dragged down the stability of the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and monetary sector.  \par \par \uc2 The rupiah has been picking up again this week, following Susilo's announcement on his new \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  line-up -- particularly the comeback of former finance minister Boediono as chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister -- thus boosting market confidence.  \par \par \uc2 In the meeting, the businesspeople also highlighted problems such as strange regulations, lack of contract sanctity involving the government, state enterprises and the private sector, as well as unfavorable \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and labor laws.  \par \par \uc2 The need to improve governance within the bureaucracy was also emphasized in the meeting, with the executives suggesting the president immediately replace "unproductive" bureaucrats who often disrupted the operation of private sector companies.  \par \par \uc2 "There is also a concern from the businesspeople over the slow process in replacing troublesome bureaucrats in several key institutions, which have caused ineffective governance and discouraged investment," said John.  \par \par \uc2 Boediono pledged that he would take concrete and immediate actions to follow-up on the suggestions and complaints from the businesses so the government would not appear to be a "no-action-talk-only" entity.  \par \par \uc2 "Should there be no real action to address the businesspeople's complaints in the foreseeable future, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  is entitled to be cynical," he said in a post-meeting press conference.  \par \par \uc2 To cater to investors' needs, both local and foreign, they will have a regular meeting with Susilo every four months at separate events starting in January.  \par \par \uc2 I-box Foreign company executives attending the meeting: Name Company Position Peter Coleman ExxonMobil Indonesia President Director Francisco Noriega Cemex Indonesia Chief representative Giuseppe Nicolosi Ernst & Young CEO  \par \par \uc2 Indonesia Hans-Josef Schill Bayer Indonesia CEO Leonard Van Hien Jardine Matheson Country chairman  \par \par \uc2 Group Indonesia Sachio Yamazaki Toyota Motor President Director  \par \par \uc2 Manufacturing Indonesia Michihiko Kanegae Sumitomo Indonesia President Director J. Francois Fichaux BNP Paribas Indonesia Country director Christopher K. Cornille Cabot Indonesia President Director John Harrison Asuransi Jiwa President Director  \par \par \uc2 Manulife Indonesia Low Sin Leng Sembcorp Industry Senior executive  \par \par \uc2 director Luigi Carlo Gastel Pirelli-Telecom President Director  \par \par \uc2 Italia Group Martin King HM Sampoerna President Director Richard Baker Ford Motor Indonesia President Director Simon Wilson Macquarie Bank Vice President Stuart Dean GE International President Director  \par \par \uc2 Operation Yasuo Ichimura Itochu Indonesia President Director Tim Leissner Goldman Sachs Senior managing  \par \par \uc2 director Joe C. Bartlet American Chamber of President  \par \par \uc2 Commerce and Industry Koki Hirota JBIC Chief representative Kosuke Imashimizu Jetro Jakarta President Peter Fanning International Business President  \par \par \uc2 Chamber  \par \par \uc2 Source: State Secretariat  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020051210e1ca00002\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
