\par\par \b \uc2 Reform in  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  regime not going anywhere   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 1,023 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 December 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 14\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Rising \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  expectation over a substantial reform in the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime seems to be fading away now as vested interests within the Ministry of Finance's Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  have stalled the deliberation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law amendments.   \par \par \uc2 With the delayed reform, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law enforcement and corruption within the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office have spawned uncontrollably, scaring away foreign investors at a time when the country is in dire need of investment in order to create more jobs.   \par \par \uc2 The good intention shown by President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono to accommodate the needs of the business community during the drafting of the amendments, by involving the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin), has not received a warm welcome from \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials.   \par \par \uc2 "There is actually progress in \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform, in the sense that there is already good will from the Susilo administration. But implementation has not been easy following opposition from the bureaucracy level," said senior auditor John A. Prasetio, who is also Kadin vice chairman for international \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cooperation.   \par \par \uc2 Bureaucrats who remain in power, despite a change in the country's leadership, maintain the status quo for their own interests or those of the group.   \par \par \uc2 There was hope early this year for an overhaul in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  system when representatives from Kadin and the Ministry of Finance's Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  agreed to jointly draft \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law amendments.   \par \par \uc2 The revisions included Law No. 16/2000 on general \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  arrangements and procedures, Law No. 17/2000 on income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law No. 18/2000 on value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) on goods and services and luxury sales \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 As the draft revisions were seen to accommodate the interests of both the business community and the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate, the amendments were then signed by President Susilo and submitted to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  for deliberation.   \par \par \uc2 However, the amendments, which were initially hailed as business-friendly, were later found to contain unfavorable articles, which granted more authority to \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials, who are prone to power abuse.   \par \par \uc2 There was outrage among business communities after they found out that the amendments contained changes altered unilaterally by the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials when they were about to be submitted to the President.   \par \par \uc2 Even though the House has yet to start deliberations on the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the general \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- including foreign businesspeople -- has expressed grave concerns over several new provisions.   \par \par \uc2 Part of the content includes the stipulation of criminal sanctions for simple \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  assessment errors, such as forgetting to completely fill in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  form.   \par \par \uc2 The requirements and procedures for \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  examination and audits also remain relaxed, without a prescribed time limit and without a specified scope for audit work, thereby putting taxpayers at the mercy of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  auditors, who have long been perceived as among the most corrupt \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials.   \par \par \uc2 Taxpayers are also put in a weaker legal position in any \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  disputes with \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials, creating an unbalanced position between taxpayers and officials, especially when the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office can confiscate assets and freeze bank accounts over any alleged \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  evasion attempts.   \par \par \uc2 Chairman of the International Business Chamber (IBC) Peter Fanning said there was a need for the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office to have sufficient powers to fulfill its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection duties, but not at a level where those powers could be abused.   \par \par \uc2 "Equality should mean that taxpayers have the right to enjoy easier \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rebate procedures and a clear and sufficient channel for filing complaints besides their obligation to pay \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "If the bills are not revised, we believe that it will scare away potential investors and make existing investors consider leaving," he added.   \par \par \uc2 The opposition has not only caused delay in the deliberation of the bills, but more importantly it has also forced the government to delay the overhaul in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime next year. As the deliberation is expected to start early next year, the government is now hoping that the reform can start in 2007.   \par \par \uc2 With intensified opposition from the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government eventually agreed to accommodate the request for a more friendly \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime during the deliberation, especially under the new finance minister.   \par \par \uc2 President Susilo appointed former state minister of national development planning Sri Mulyani Indrawati as the new minister of finance, replacing Jusuf Anwar on Dec.5, with an aim to help improve the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition as well as clearing ways for a more friendly \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime.   \par \par \uc2 Aside from the debacle in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  bills, the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate has also been slow in improving its service. This is apparent from the low number of large \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  offices (LTOs), which are being set up under a relatively new system for the "clean" and efficient collection and administration of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate has been planning to apply the LTO administrative system in all of its \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  offices nationwide since 2002. However, in practice, only two offices are equipped with LTO services this year, or five offices in total.   \par \par \uc2 The directorate is also taking a short cut in trying to enlarge the taxpayer base by applying a nationwide arbitrary taxpayer registration scheme, which is based on the verification of individuals' assets and financial transactions.   \par \par \uc2 To increase the number of taxpayers, the directorate has been sending out millions of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  number application forms to those it has categorized as potential taxpayers, claiming that it will increase the number of taxpayers to 10 million this year.   \par \par \uc2 As of the end of last year, only 3.67 million of the country's 220 million population paid \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- just 13.5 percent of the Gross National Product (GNP) -- one of the lowest among major Asian economies.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate claims that with an increase in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  base this year, the government is expected to reap an additional Rp 5 trillion (US$490 million) from the added number of taxpayers this year.   \par \par \uc2 However, the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  may not be aware that some of the 10 million taxpayers claimed by the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate may only exist on paper as the directorate could not verify the actual number of people who are truly paying their \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020051227e1cr0000y\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
