\par\par \b \uc2 Loans, projects to spur growth   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi A. Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 542 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 December 2005\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2005 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 To stimulate higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth through the utilization of the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government is to speed up the disbursement of massive loan commitments from overseas creditors within the first semester of next year.   \par \par \uc2 The amount of the loans that will soon be disbursed include some Rp 9.9 trillion (US$1.01 billion) of program loans and around Rp 25.2 trillion of project loans, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Boediono said after a Cabinet meeting on Wednesday.   \par \par \uc2 "If we can speed up the disbursement, it will help drive higher \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth next year, as well as reducing the revolving impact of this year's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown," said Boediono in a press conference.   \par \par \uc2 The government will accelerate and maximize its \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for projects during the first semester of next year to help stimulate the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , with the private sector's financing access likely to be hampered by the current tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  applied by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  amid the high inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Boediono is optimistic that the private sector will revive investment in the second semester after the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  starts to gradually lower its lending rates.   \par \par \uc2 The government will also reduce bureaucracy barriers in order to speed up the tender process of projects offered during February's Infrastructure Summit.   \par \par \uc2 Few investors are interested in taking part in the tender due to reasons ranging from bureaucratic constraints to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over land clearance procedures.   \par \par \uc2 Of the total of 91 projects worth around $22.5 billion on offer in the first edition of the summit, only four even managed to get to the bidding stage, and only one project is currently being carried out.   \par \par \uc2 "We will see what kind of problems are discouraging investors from participating. We will ensure them that the problems will be settled as soon as possible and give ways for speeding up the project construction next semester," said Boediono.   \par \par \uc2 Indonesia, Southeast Asia's largest \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , is facing an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  downturn this year after inflation accelerated to 18.4 percent between January and November, the highest in six years, largely due to the government's decision to raise fuel prices on Oct. 1.   \par \par \uc2 To mitigate the inflationary pressures, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has aggressively raised its benchmark interest rate six times in the last six months, with the current rate at 12.75 percent.   \par \par \uc2 Higher inflation and \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  have contributed to a slowdown in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth and put the brakes on the country's consumption-driven \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as both consumer loans and credit for business expansion become more expensive.   \par \par \uc2 As part of an effort to anticipate a possible decline in state revenues from \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  following a downturn faced by the business community, the government is also planning to provide several \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives and smoothen \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  payments and reimbursements.   \par \par \uc2 The Cabinet meeting also discussed issues related to security and the social conditions next year, with Coordinating Minister for Security and Political Affairs Widodo Adi Sucipto highlighting some of the government's focus.   \par \par \uc2 "In general, we will remain focused on settling issues related to terrorism, corruption and drug trafficking next year. The efforts to combat these three crimes will be intensified with an emphasis on results," said Widodo.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020051229e1ct00005\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
