\par\par \b \uc2 Govt plans crucial policies for 2006   \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi Akhmad Witular and Mustaqim , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 590 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 January 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The government will push through a number of crucial policies this year to promote robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activity for the private sector and help spur growth, with most efforts centered on providing certainty and stability for the business community.   \par \par \uc2 The efforts will include reform in the bureaucracy, revisions to the labor law, rearrangement of the management of provincial \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  and improved integrity in the capital market sector.   \par \par \uc2 Vice President Jusuf Kalla said on Monday the government would try to reinvigorate the real sector by ensuring the maintenance of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social stability as well as better security.   \par \par \uc2 "What investors buy here is an expectation. We can assure them that expectations are running high this year for an improvement in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Kalla told industry players after opening this year's first trading day at the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX).   \par \par \uc2 Kalla was accompanied by Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Boediono, Minister of Finance Sri Mulyani, chairman of the Capital Market Supervisory Agency Darmin Nasution and JSX president director Erry Firmansyah.   \par \par \uc2 Kalla said the business community should start taking into account such expectations immediately as the government had already disbursed some Rp 204 trillion (US$20.8 billion) worth of projects from the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to provincial governments.   \par \par \uc2 With the disbursement, the government expects to help revive the slowdown in the activity of the real sector, as a result of the 2005 \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown.   \par \par \uc2 To support the activities, the government plans to issue in the next two or three months an official guide book for the bureaucracy in providing \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  services, which will include a timeframe for processing a document and its exact price.   \par \par \uc2 "Kickbacks within the civil service are mostly caused by the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  set out by the government bureaucrats on the ground. If there is a time target and clear price guidance, such practices will definitely be reduced," said Kalla.   \par \par \uc2 In the labor sector, the government expects a draft revision of the labor law could be delivered to the legislators for deliberation in February or March. Several articles in the law, which require a company to pay compensation for workers filing for resignation are likely to be amended to encourage companies to hire more workers.   \par \par \uc2 "There will be a new philosophy in the revised labor law. It will not only prioritize those who already have a job, but also those currently unemployed. With a law that is more conducive to hiring new workers, the private sector will help alleviate unemployment," said Kalla.   \par \par \uc2 The business community will also be protected from \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  created by the administrations in the provinces and regencies, especially on the problem related to regional fees and \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which contribute unnecessarily to the higher cost of doing business across the archipelago.   \par \par \uc2 "Several central government regulations will be issued soon to prevent local administrations from issuing the fees and \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  that are merely a burden on the business community. This will not only reduce the cost of doing business, but will also create more business certainty," said Sri Mulyani.   \par \par \uc2 The government will also start reviewing several capital market regulations that provide windows of opportunity for irregularities. "The integrity of the capital market should be upgraded. Loopholes in regulations will be reviewed, and players should also start showing a good attitude in improving the integrity," said Sri Mulyani.   \par \par \uc2 The Jakarta stock market ended the day higher by 9.07 points, or 0.8 percent, to 1,171.71. It was the largest gain in two weeks.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060103e21300012\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
