\par\par \b \uc2 Massive overhaul needed to root out graft in  \highlight22\uc2 tax \highlight\uc2  service  \b0\par\par\uc2 Rendi Akhmad Witular , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta  \par \uc2 865 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 January 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 "Jono" is a junior official in an East Jakarta \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office, and regularly parks his silver BMW sedan, which he drives from his luxury home in Cibubur, Bogor, at his friend's house in Jakarta before riding a Honda scooter on the last leg of his journey to work.  \par \par \uc2 Although possessing only a high school diploma, Jono well understands that he needs to avoid arousing \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  suspicion over the wealth he has gained from falsifying \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  documents and claims for value-added \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  (VAT) refunds.  \par \par \uc2 Jono readily admits he has been involved in this dirty work for more than five years, inflicting estimated losses on the state of around Rp 14 billion (US$1.48 million).  \par \par \uc2 While his case is just the tip of the iceberg, it highlights how the cancer of corruption has spread throughout the Directorate General of \b \highlight22\uc2 Taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 At a time when the government is in dire need of money to provide adequate \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  infrastructure and services, the relevant ministers and officials in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministries seem helpless to stamp out the graft.  \par \par \uc2 With the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  directorate general tasked this year with collecting Rp 362 trillion ($38.51 billion) in \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and a plethora of reports on corruption, the warnings from analysts that leakage of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue may amount to many trillions of rupiah annually need to be heeded by all.  \par \par \uc2 An internal report obtained by The Jakarta Post recently from a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  office shows Finance Ministry's Inspectorate General has identified a variety of corruption methods and causes.  \par \par \uc2 However, it remains unclear why the report has not been acted upon to prevent corruption in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  service, nor why it has not been taken into consideration during the drafting of the recent \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law amendment bills by the government.  \par \par \uc2 Representatives of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin) who were involved in drafting the amendments seem to have missed the big picture by merely focusing on technical matters, such as \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates and procedures.  \par \par \uc2 As highlighted in the Inspectorate General's report, corruption in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  service occurs primarily because of the service's excessive powers, including its power to set \b \highlight22\uc2 tax policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , collect \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  and supervise \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection.  \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  analyst Munir M. Ali of the University of Indonesia said the spiraling corruption in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  service had long been obvious. The spread of the cancer was helped by the fact that the service was structured in such a way that it left no room for balance or the sharing of rights.  \par \par \uc2 "Everybody should be blamed for making the directorate general excessively powerful, thus opening the way for its officials to abuse their powers. Whoever the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  chief is, corruption will continue unabated unless the service's powers are reduced," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Munir suggested the government and legislature start stripping the service of some of its powers by separating the functions of \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making, \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  collection and oversight during the upcoming deliberations on the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  law amendment bills.  \par \par \uc2 Among the laws to be amended are Law No. 16/2000 on general \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  arrangements and procedures, Law No. 17/2000 on income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Law No. 18/2000 on VAT and luxury goods \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 "Our \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  incentives and \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates are fairly competitive worldwide, on average. But investors are still reluctant to come here because of the poor implementation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  laws, which leads to a high-cost \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," said Munir.  \par \par \uc2 "China has the highest \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates in the region, but investors are still going there as they feel comfortable with the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  regime, despite the high rates. This shows that lower \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  rates and good incentives will not count too much in the absence of a good system," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Lack of transparency is also blamed for corruption in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  service, with the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  providing little in the way of rights for taxpayers to seek clarifications or explanations regarding the calculation of their \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  bills.  \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  only gives the taxpayer the "opportunity" to seek such information, instead of conferring a "right" on them to do so. This gives excessive discretion to \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials in calculating the amount of \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  owed.  \par \par \uc2 Another concern is the numerous "gray areas" in the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax legislation\b0 \highlight\uc2  that are subject to differing interpretations between \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials and taxpayers, thus opening the way to bargaining, collusion and extortion.  \par \par \uc2 As things stand at the moment, there is no institution that is capable of resolving taxpayer complaints independently, because the existing \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  tribunal does not come under the auspices of the Supreme Court but rather the Finance Ministry, with the judges' salaries being paid by the ministry.  \par \par \uc2 Taxpayers are often reluctant to appeal to the court as they are required to pay 50 percent of their alleged \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  arrears before the court will hear their cases, which can sometimes prove to be burdensome.  \par \par \uc2 "If the government is unable to immediately overhaul the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  service, it could instead speed up the establishment of modern \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  offices applying the system currently employed by the Large \b \highlight22\uc2 Tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  Office, which has proven itself to be clean and effective, said Munir.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060119e21j0000c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
