\par\par \b \uc2 Govt sizes up ways to plug PLN  \highlight22\uc2 deficit \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta, Bali  \par \uc2 643 \uc2 words\par \uc2 22 March 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 2\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono said Tuesday the government was examining ways to finance the additional \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  needed by state electricity company PT PLN this year after it decided to drop its power rate hike plan.  \par \par \uc2 The government also will push PLN to boost efficiency as well as accelerate the process of conversion of some of the company's oil-based power plants to use of gas and coal to reduce energy costs amid rising oil prices.  \par \par \uc2 Yudhoyono, speaking to reporters after a Cabinet meeting on the issue, said the power hike plan was dropped mostly because the business community was still struggling from the rise in fuel prices last year.  \par \par \uc2 "The real sector, especially industry and small and medium businesses, is still unable to cope with such rise," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Yudhoyono refused to elaborate on proposed ways to help plug the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , saying only that the government and the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  would revise the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to make the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  sustainable.  \par \par \uc2 Vice President Jusuf Kalla said late last week that he and the President had decided to scrap the plan to help avoid exerting a greater burden on the business sector and the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 . The decision came following widespread protests from businesses and lawmakers, raising concerns that proceeding with the plan could create a political backlash.  \par \par \uc2 Finance Minister Sri Mulyani Indrawati said Tuesday the government would cut several items of planned budgetary \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to cover the Rp 10.2 trillion (US$1.10 billion) additional \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  for PLN to avoid increases in the power rate.  \par \par \uc2 "The additional \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  must be covered by the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We will have to look through all of our planned expenditures again. We may consider dropping unnecessary ones and reallocate the funds for the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," she said.  \par \par \uc2 Mulyani said that should the \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  still fall short even from this reallocation, the government might have to resort to expanding the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , or by increasing the level of state revenues.  \par \par \uc2 "But the final decision will be taken during the revision of this year's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with the House. We will have to see the process then," she said.  \par \par \uc2 Yudhoyono also said that the government would ease several regulations concerning the construction of new power plants, including cutting the 800 days for the negotiation period, to encourage the participation of the private sector.  \par \par \uc2 "The country will need some 40,000 megawatt (MW) of power plants by 2010 to prevent a shortage in the power supply. At present, the capacity is only around 28,000 MW. The future plants will use gas and coal to help slash power rates," he said.  \par \par \uc2 Energy and Mineral Resources Minister Purnomo Yusgiantoro said the 12,000 MW of power plants would be constructed soon, with half of the capacity to be handled by PLN and the remainder by the private sector.  \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, a senior official at the Asian Development Bank said the decision to drop the plan would produce more problems in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because it would create new \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the investment climate.  \par \par \uc2 "It really gave a good sign showing that the Indonesian government really cares about its people. However, it will cause tremendous impacts on the market and investors' confidence," said Patrick Giraud, ADB director of infrastructure division, on the sidelines of an investment seminar Tuesday in Nusa Dua, Bali.  \par \par \uc2 He said it was acceptable for the government to instruct PLN to improve its efficiency, "but is PLN able to improve efficiency at the level of the additional cost burden they have to face".  \par \par \uc2 ADB, he said, was working with the government to formulate a special technical and financial assistance program to make PLN more efficient. "We will meet with the government's team next week and will design the proper programs to do so," Giraud added.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060322e23m00006\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
