\par\par \b \uc2 Protests not xenophobic: Boediono   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 535 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 March 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 3\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Recent protests against U.S. mining companies operating here reflect valid \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  concerns about the benefits of mining investment and are not xenophobic, Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Boediono says.   \par \par \uc2 His comments late Thursday came as the U.S. envoy here warned that the campaign against foreign companies here could be damaging to foreign investment in the country.   \par \par \uc2 "I don't think it's an indication of a rise in antiforeign investment or something like that," Boediono said as quoted by Dow Jones .   \par \par \uc2 "It's an expression among the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  for a fairer share of (investment) benefits (and) it's a legitimate demand that we, the government and the business community can work together to address," he added, speaking on the sidelines of a business gathering held by the United States-Indonesia Society (Usindo).   \par \par \uc2 The local operations of U.S. mining giants including Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., Newmont Mining Corp., and oil giant ExxonMobil Corp. have recently been the target of protests.   \par \par \uc2 Protesters burned Newmont's exploration camp on Sumbawa island in West Nusa Tenggara on March 19. No one was injured in the attack, located about 60 kilometers from the company's US$2 billion Batu Hijau copper-gold mine operation, but the company was forced to close the camp and suspend exploration activities in the area.   \par \par \uc2 The incident followed a deadly anti-PT Freeport Indonesia protest on March 16 in Papua, in which five security officers were killed. Protesters are demanding the closure of the world's largest gold mining operation, which was forced to temporarily suspend operation last month.   \par \par \uc2 ExxonMobil Corp. also has faced protests, including from politicians opposed to its appointment as general manager to run the day-to-day operations of the lucrative Cepu oil block. In the latter days of the dispute between ExxonMobil and state oil and gas firm Pertamina, supporters of Pertamina warned against selling national assets to a foreign company.   \par \par \uc2 Boediono dismissed fears the protests represented anti-U.S. sentiment or xenophobic sentiment.   \par \par \uc2 "It's not (an expression of) rising anti-foreigner, anti-foreign investment, anti-American or anti-American investment," he said.   \par \par \uc2 "It's a form of growing awareness among the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  here that business and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities by domestic and foreign companies must produce tangible benefits for ordinary people."   \par \par \uc2 However, U.S. Ambassador to Indonesia B. Lynn Pascoe warned the campaign against foreign investors was damaging the country's investment climate, particularly when badly needed foreign direct investment was finally beginning to pick up after the devastating 1997 financial crisis.   \par \par \uc2 "... I am appalled at much of the rhetoric and the demonstrations that we have seen over the past few days opposing foreign investment in Indonesia," Pascoe said at the Usindo event.   \par \par \uc2 "How can someone have missed the fact that foreign investment has been the critical element of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth for many countries in the region ...."   \par \par \uc2 Investment inflows also have been hampered by investors' perceptions of legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , rampant corruption and shabby infrastructure.   \par \par \uc2 The government is currently working hard to attract $150 billion in fresh investment to help finance infrastructure development to meet an average annual 6.6 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  expansion target for 2004-2009.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060325e23p00007\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
