\par\par \b \uc2 Three million commuters make traffic even worse   \b0\par\par\uc2 Adianto P. Simamora , The Jakarta Post, Jakarta   \par \uc2 983 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 April 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 9\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Jakarta as the center of a megacity - that was the concept floated by Governor Sutiyoso. But is now the best time for its execution? The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  is examining Jakarta's position as capital of Indonesia, and many of the city's neighbors are ignorant of the potential benefits -- and drawbacks -- of being part of a megacity. The Jakarta Post looks at the much-hyped megacity idea -- through the eyes of the city's neighbors.   \par \par \uc2 Rina Gunawan, a Bogor resident who works as a secretary in Jakarta, leaves home in the morning and arrives back home in the evening when it is still dark.   \par \par \uc2 It takes the 29-year-old over two hours to get to work. After a full day in the office, she then manages to drive to Depok for her undergraduate classes at the University of Indonesia before going home.   \par \par \uc2 "I usually get home just after 11 p.m. I'm getting used to the traffic congestion; I do it because Jakarta offers career opportunities and better pay," Rina, a graduate of the Indonesian Management and Secretarial Academy (ASMI) in East Jakarta, told The Jakarta Post .   \par \par \uc2 Rina is one of at least three million people from Bogor, Depok, Tangerang, Bekasi, Puncak and Cianjur who have the same reason for commuting to Jakarta -- the country's most heavily populated city -- every day.   \par \par \uc2 Coping with the influx of unskilled workers has been a test for Jakarta and made it vulnerable to a host of problems, including many social problems.   \par \par \uc2 High commuter numbers have exacerbated traffic congestion, particularly at peak times, and resulted in air pollution reaching dangerous levels.   \par \par \uc2 Moreover, Jakarta's attempts to remedy the situation, such as through the busway and three-in-one system, which was introduced to encourage car pooling among people from the same neighborhoods, have not been as successful as planned   \par \par \uc2 Thus, many experts are also pessimistic about the proposed Mass Rapid Transit system, as it will only as it will only operate in Jakarta areas.   \par \par \uc2 With a population of 12 million during the day, Jakarta has to manage 6,000 tons of garbage daily. The frustrated-city administration spent huge amounts of money to reduce the volume of waste from Jakarta being dumped in neighboring Bekasi.   \par \par \uc2 The other problem is the threat of floods, mostly during the rainy season, with the floodwaters traveling from upstream areas such as Bogor, Puncak, Bekasi and Depok.   \par \par \uc2 Given the long-standing problems, Jakarta Governor Sutiyoso come up with the "novel" idea of integrated urban planning through the establishment of a "megacity" covering Jakarta, Bogor, Depok, Tangerang, Bekasi and Cianjur, to be known by its unwieldly Indonesian acronym as "Jabodetabekjur".   \par \par \uc2 The idea, which was first suggested by former governor Ali Sadikin in the seventies, had earlier been firmly rejected by both administrations and residents of Jakarta's surrounding areas.   \par \par \uc2 Tangerang regency is part of Banten province, while the four other cities are located in West Java province.   \par \par \uc2 However, after months of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the administrations in the local government areas surrounding Jakarta finally accepted the megacity concept in early March.   \par \par \uc2 A \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  working committee is currently discussing a bill on the governance of Jakarta, which will deal with the megacity concept.   \par \par \uc2 Experts say that to make the megacity project work, the spatial functions of the region need to be properly allocated, especially given that there is still a lot of agricultural land to be found within the boundaries of the proposed megacity.   \par \par \uc2 Noted economist Emil Salim has proposed an "ants and sugar" plan for Jakarta and its neighbors.   \par \par \uc2 He says that if the "sugar" is distributed to Jakarta's neighbors, then the ants (residents) will automatically move to other areas in pursuit of the sugar.   \par \par \uc2 Lukman Mokoginta, chairman of the Center for Social, Environmental and Urban Studies, said that the creation of the megacity would have to be preceded by a determination of the functions of each of the cities involved.   \par \par \uc2 "Bekasi and Tangerang are suitable for industrial development, Depok should be designed as an education and residential center, while the upstream areas of Bogor, Puncak and Cianjur would maintain their agricultural and tourism functions," he explained.   \par \par \uc2 He said that large-scale and heavy industry could be located farther away from Bekasi and Tangerang cities in places such as in Cikarang or Karawaci so as to avoid too much groundwater being absorbed by industry.   \par \par \uc2 "The most important thing is that the megacity concept must also consider the impact on the environment. Each city has to properly manage its environment," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Lukman, who is currently a special advisor to the State Minister for the Environment, said that Depok must allocate part of its surface area as a green belt.   \par \par \uc2 Meanwhile, Bogor, the source of several rivers that flow through Jakarta, needed to avoid the siting of factories along its river banks so as to prevent pollution, he said.   \par \par \uc2 "Through proper spatial planning, investors wanting to do business will find it easier to choose the right locations," he explained.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the Jakarta needed to be developed as a service city.   \par \par \uc2 Lukman, who is also a former Jakarta councilor, added that in all scenarios, improvement of the transportation system linking all the cities had to be prioritized.   \par \par \uc2 "If the transportation system is adequate, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities will proceed smoothly, and people will be able to travel to earn a living. They won't all need to rush to Jakarta," he explained.   \par \par \uc2 He said that the establishment of the proposed megacity would contribute significantly to the incomes of the local administrations and their residents.   \par \par \uc2 "I believe, five years after the megacity has been established, significant additional income will be accruing to the local administrations. The people's purchasing power will also increase, and thus more investors will be attracted to do business in the area," he said.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060424e24o0000v\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
