\par\par \b \uc2 The oil crunch   \b0\par\par\uc2 737 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 April 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 Government assurances that there will not be another fuel price hike soon, despite the steady rise in global oil prices to as high as US$75/barrel earlier this week, do not mean it is business as usual in our energy sector. Industrial users, which buy fuel at market prices, will feel the impact of higher oil prices next month when state-owned oil company Pertamina sets its monthly fuel prices.   \par \par \uc2 True, it is too early to revise upward the subsidized prices of gasoline, automotive diesel oil and kerosene, which are based on the $57/barrel oil price average assumed for the entire \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, to set the total fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy\b0 \highlight\uc2  at Rp 54.3 trillion ($6.5 billion).   \par \par \uc2 After all, it is not only the fundamental forces of supply and demand that have caused the steady, steep rise in international oil prices to over $70 since early this month. The demand for oil has risen markedly in Asia due to robust \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth in the region, especially in China and India, but this expansion has not been so drastic as to generate such steep increases in oil prices.   \par \par \uc2 In fact, market speculation, propelled by concerns over geopolitical \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , notably the West's nuclear dispute with Iran, and supply constraints in Iraq, Nigeria and Mexico, has been the main reason behind the high price rise over the last three weeks.   \par \par \uc2 Hence, it is wise for the government to wait and closely monitor price developments in the next few months before shocking the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  with another fuel price increase. During the first quarter, for example, global oil prices still ranged between $61 and $62 a barrel. Only since early this month have prices skyrocketed to more than $70.   \par \par \uc2 However, official assurances ruling out the possibility of an imminent fuel price hike are meant only as a political statement to calm the market and prevent speculation. These assurances by no means imply the government can simply sit and relax and continue with "business as usual" in the energy sector.   \par \par \uc2 On the contrary, the latest oil price rises should again serve as a rude wake-up call to the government to fully realize the country's vulnerability to oil price rises due to our overdependence on oil energy. The intensity of oil use in energy consumption, or the share of oil in primary energy consumption in Indonesia, is the highest among ASEAN countries.   \par \par \uc2 These latest developments should be an alarm to the government to immediately launch an adequate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  response designed to conserve energy and accelerate the diversification of our energy sources into natural gas, coal, geothermal power and such renewable energies as bio-diesel and ethanol.   \par \par \uc2 As a net oil importer with a very high intensity of oil use in its primary energy consumption, Indonesia is extremely vulnerable to oil price rises, which affect our output, inflation and balance of payments, as well as \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  position. Higher oil prices squeeze income and domestic market demand, impose strong inflationary pressure and exact \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  consequences in the form of larger fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 It is pleasing to note the government used a market pricing mechanism to encourage oil conservation by doubling fuel prices last October, and has designed a crash program for the building of more than 10,000 megawatts in new power generation within three years to minimize state power company PLN's heavy dependence on oil-based generation.   \par \par \uc2 But plainly absent in the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  responses to our vulnerabilities to oil price volatility are \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures to force the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  and industrial companies to conserve oil and electricity. The government has failed to deliver on its promise last year to introduce \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures such as higher luxury sales \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on high-capacity cars and higher vehicle registration \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on people who own more than one car.   \par \par \uc2 The government should realize that to be effective, energy diversification and fuel efficiency programs should be enforced under a special law that stipulates compulsory and voluntary conservation measures, complete with \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and financial incentives for the development of renewable energy sources. The government has at its disposal a variety of instruments such as \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  credits and subsidized or low-interest loans through which energy efficiency improvements can be promoted.   \par \par \uc2 But most important is that energy conservation and diversification should be integrated in a comprehensive, long-term program to provide legal certainty and a strong directive to energy development investors and energy users.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060427e24r0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
