\par\par \b \uc2 President's plan to form new  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  task force slammed  \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta  \par \uc2 499 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 May 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 Experts have criticized a plan by President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono to form a new working unit to help address the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems and improve the investment climate, saying the only thing the business community needed was a concrete and unified \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 Yudhoyono should concentrate on making concrete policies and maximizing the existing resources, the chairman of the Indonesian National \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Recovery Committee, Sofjan Wanandi, said Sunday.  \par \par \uc2 "The planned unit is basically a good idea. But I doubt that the President will implement the input provided by the unit. He cannot even implement existing plans and resolve the problems already conveyed by the business community," he said.  \par \par \uc2 In a Cabinet meeting Friday, Yudhoyono came up with the idea to form a unit tasked with providing input on ways to address \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems at home, and also to supervise the implementation of the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies.  \par \par \uc2 "The unit is part of a tool attached to the President. Its task will be to smooth reform in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , administration, state enterprises and small and medium businesses," Coordinating Minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Boediono said after the meeting.  \par \par \uc2 The unit, which will be formed through presidential decree, will consist of professional economists and businesspeople. There are reports that former Cabinet secretary and former attorney general Marsilam Simanjuntak has been tapped to lead the unit.  \par \par \uc2 Boediono said the unit also would help the government improve the business climate and ensure that problems faced by the business community would be addressed effectively and promptly.  \par \par \uc2 Economist Aviliani said such a unit would be a waste of energy because the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies applied by Yudhoyono were no different from those of previous administrations.  \par \par \uc2 "The real sector needs a breakthrough in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies, not more advisers or new plans. If the unit can only provide similar programs to those already arranged by the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers, it would be just another waste," she said.  \par \par \uc2 Since taking office in October 2004, experts say Yudhoyono has failed to introduce any substantial \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies to help encourage investment, despite having already replaced his chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister and finance minister.  \par \par \uc2 Local and international investors remain concerned about illegal fees, a complex bureaucracy, legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  and unfriendly local administrations, with few signs their concerns are being addressed.  \par \par \uc2 While Yudhoyono and his \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  team blame external factors as the main cause of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  problems, the business community sees little effort being made to lessen the impact by concretely addressing the problems.  \par \par \uc2 "The problems have already been laid out by the business community. What Yudhoyono should do is execute the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  policies already planned. He should be quick because the real sector is not developing and unemployment is soaring," Sofjan said.  \par \par \uc2 Indonesia is facing an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  slowdown with sluggish growth in the real sector, which has seen the number of unemployed rise to 40.1 million, or 37 percent of the country's 107 million workforce.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060529e25t0000x\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw139\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal2085\pichgoal600
