s will be on a legal umbrella, territory, facilities and infrastructure, integrated services, and their institutionalization.   \par \par \uc2 According to Jamin, referring to the special \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  zones in Shenzen, Shuzou and Hainan, China, the three special \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  zones are not run all at the same time, but part by part, and they have achieved great progress as they are now.   \par \par \uc2 And Sianturi even said that actually there was no need to refer to such project so far away from home, the nearest example is the successful running of the SEZ in Bintan.   \par \par \uc2 He said that a model SEZ is already in operation in the Lagoi integrated tourist area and the Lobam Industrial Estate currently producing some Rp48 billion per year, which is more than half of the total earnings of Karimun regency.   \par \par \uc2 The growth of the two regions was started in 1990 with a memorandum of understaning on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  cooperation under the framework of Singapura-Johor-Indonesia Growth Triangle, followed by Presidential Decree on the Riau Province Development Coordinating Team. The team formed by virtue of the Presidential Decree has 21 members from the different relevant ministries.   \par \par \uc2 The climax of the discourse was the issuance of Decree of the Minister of Finance no. 60 known as the July package of 2005 as legal basis of Lagoi and Lobam, and the Batam-Bintan-Karimun bonded zone plus.   \par \par \uc2 Jamin said that while it must be admitted that Bintan has its shortfalls, the two special \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  zones Lagoi and Lobam produced Rp48 billion.   \par \par \uc2 And those places already have facilities and infrastructure of international standard like ports, power lines, clean water, roads, and telecommunications network.   \par \par \uc2 "All built by the private sector," he added.   \par \par \uc2 L