\par\par \b \uc2 Sharia bylaws a panacea for legal system?  \b0\par\par\uc2 Mohammad Yazid , Jakarta  \par \uc2 704 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 June 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 7\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 Somebody who develops serious health problems and expects a total recovery immediately can only count on a "miracle". This is perhaps comparable to the present situation in Indonesia, where numerous sharia-inspired ordinances have emerged since the implementation of regional autonomy.  \par \par \uc2 Like a panacea, the bylaws were passed in the hope of overcoming a variety of problems promptly. Sadly, this has not happened. Like a doctor handling a chronically ill patient, he must consider other conditions and factors when prescribing medicine. Unless these things are taken into account, it is only expected that the ordinances will cause controversy and complication.  \par \par \uc2 The issue of these sharia-inspired bylaws comes to the fore amid much \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 , notably lax law enforcement that falls far short of expectations and declining \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence in the government, the legal system and the law itself. This has resulted in pessimism and has moved people to take the law into their own hands.  \par \par \uc2 Consequently, many people have gotten the impression that the implementation of such regional bylaws leads to anarchy. An example is the adoption of the controversial Regional \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  No. 8/2005 on the prohibition of prostitution in Tangerang, Banten. This has given rise to fears that innocent women will be targeted by law enforcers, particularly women who work at night. The fears were justified after a restaurant employee in Cengkareng, Lilis Lindawati, was wrongfully arrested and accused of being a prostitute.  \par \par \uc2 Although this bylaw was well intended, it should not be overlooked that prostitution cannot be addressed by an ordinance alone, because the problem is very complex, involving unemployment and an ever-worsening \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 Sharia-inspired bylaws have bred disagreement not only among Muslims but also between Muslims and non-Muslims. This is not a problem as long as the debate is based on \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  interests rather than group interests.  \par \par \uc2 Saying the bylaws contravene the Constitution and state ideology Pancasila, 56 legislators in the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  have proposed a review of the regional regulations.  \par \par \uc2 To some extent, however, the opposition to the bylaws has triggered tension between those groups who support and those who oppose the ordinances.  \par \par \uc2 As pointed out by Nur Hidayat Wahid, speaker of the People's Consultative Assembly, in the latest edition of Tempo magazine there are two extreme views that cannot grasp the meaning of sharia. The first arises when sharia is understood only literally and textually, which causes anarchic behavior. The second appears when Islamophobia prevails, as evident when people suspect everything, like the pornography bill, is a move to formalize Islamic law.  \par \par \uc2 Opposition to the bylaws should not kill mutual respect. If such ordinances are founded on universal values, like those banning prostitution and narcotics, they will certainly win support from all groups.  \par \par \uc2 Even without heated debate, some regional regulations have failed to take effect because local communities and authorities face a lot of constraints in implementing them, such as the bylaw banning becak (three-wheel pedicabs) in certain areas and the smoking ban in Jakarta.  \par \par \uc2 One thing that should be remembered is natural selection, which cannot be resisted by any group. Any bylaw that fails to live up to the growing aspirations of the people will be short-lived and difficult to implement.  \par \par \uc2 "If a \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  creates disharmony and disrupts social relations, it must be reviewed. Sharia-inspired bylaws are emerging in a time of euphoria and it won't last long. Regional authorities will find it difficult to apply them with their present law enforcers. Even in Aceh, with so many Arab words, there's a lot of cannabis," said Syafii Ma'arif, former chairman of the Muslim group Muhammadiyah.  \par \par \uc2 In order to guarantee the proper acceptance and implementation of well-intended bylaws, there are several simple points to ponder. It is imperative that the regulations serve \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  interests rather than group priorities. They should consider the sincere and pure aspirations of the pluralistic society. Bylaw drafters need wisdom and, above all, the ordinances they produce cannot oppose the spirit of Pancasila, which is the nation's supreme law.  \par \par \uc2 The writer is a staff member on The Jakarta Post 's Opinion Desk. He can be reached at yazid@thejakartapost.com .  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060623e26n0000o\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
