\par\par \b \uc2 Foreign oil firms to be allowed to buy, sell biofuel  \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta  \par \uc2 571 \uc2 words\par \uc2 9 August 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 13\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post  \par \par \uc2 A regulatory package will soon be put in place to allow foreign oil firms such as Petronas of Malaysia and Shell of the Netherlands to distribute biofuel so as to boost competition on the domestic market, it was revealed Tuesday.  \par \par \uc2 The coordinating minister for the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's deputy for agriculture and marine affairs, Bayu Krisnamurti, said foreign firms would be allowed to buy biofuel from growers/producers and sell it back to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  as long as it was being sold for transportation purposes.  \par \par \uc2 "That way, consumers will benefit from fair prices due to the competition, while on the other hand investors and growers will continue to be interested in biofuel production," he said on the sidelines of a seminar organized by the Indonesian Biodiversity Foundation.  \par \par \uc2 The government had earlier appointed state oil and gas firm PT Pertamina and state power firm PT PLN to serve as standby buyers of biofuel.  \par \par \uc2 Derom Bangun, executive chairman of the Indonesian Palm Oil Producers Association, said that the proposal to allow firms other than Pertamina to purchase biofuel would encourage investors to construct biofuel plants.  \par \par \uc2 "Many firms are reluctant to build biofuel plants because they are afraid that Pertamina will be given the exclusive right to buy their products at low prices. With competition, the oil companies will have to purchase the biofuel at fair prices," he said.  \par \par \uc2 He hoped that with a large number of biofuel plants in the pipeline, the country would be able to achieve its biofuel production target of 13 million tons per year by 2009.  \par \par \uc2 According to the Investment Coordinating Board (BKPM), 15 companies have applied for licenses to produce a total of one million tons of bio-diesel per year.  \par \par \uc2 The companies include PT Wahana Abdi Tirta, PT Anugrah Inti Gemanusa, PT Sari Dumai Sejati, PT Indo Bio fuels, PT Artha Trans Jaya, PT Asanagro Agung Jaya, PT Wilmar Bioenergi Indonesia, a joint venture between PT Bakrie Sumatera Plantation and PT Rekayasa Industri, PT Musimas, PT Karya Prajona Nelayan, PT Biodiesel Indonesia, a joint venture between PT Rekayasa and Pertamina, PT Astra Agro Lestari (2), PT Eterindo Jawa Timur, and PT Energi Alternatif Indonesia.  \par \par \uc2 As for the government, it plans to construct eight bio-diesel plants, with each having a production capacity of between 3,000 and 6,000 tons per year.  \par \par \uc2 Last week, President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono held meetings with Malaysia's top energy companies to encourage them to invest in the Indonesian bio-energy sector.  \par \par \uc2 Speaking after the meetings, Minister for Energy and Mineral Resources Purnomo Yusgiantoro said that a committee would soon start work on drawing up regulations that would ease the way for foreign companies to invest in the bio-energy sector.  \par \par \uc2 The rapid increase in global oil prices, which reached more than US$70 per barrel recently, in part on account of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the Middle East, has prompted the government to turn to the much cheaper and more environmentally friendly biofuel.  \par \par \uc2 The use of biofuel is expected to account for 10 percent of the country's energy consumption by 2009, enough to significantly reduce the burden on the national \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  arising from fuel \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidy spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 Biofuel is a renewable energy resource and is produced from such crops as the castor-oil plant, oil palm, cassava and sugarcane, all of which can easily be grown in Indonesia. (05)  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060809e28900016\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Investment on mining declines   \b0\par\par\uc2 270 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 August 2006\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 Bisnis Indonesia   \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Indonesian investment on mining industry has declined in the last ten years, and it will lower the mining exploitation and even will stop it one day.   \par \par \uc2 The Senior \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  Minister Boediono said that it was due to the unfavorable investment climate during the transition era of reformation.   \par \par \uc2 "Among other problems is the legal \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  due to the disharmonizing of laws on forest, landscaping, regional autonomy and \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he wrote in a written speech read by his Deputy on Energy, Mineral Resources and Forestry Wimpy S Tjetjep on the national symposium on "Searching for Resolution Model on Mining Conflict" in Jakarta yesterday.   \par \par \uc2 The report of PricewaterhouseCoopers (PwC) said that the new investment and the business expansion on mining sector in 2005 were lower than that on the previous years. The \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  on exploration in Indonesia during 1995-1997 was US$40 million, and down to US$19 million in 1998-2000 and only US$7 million in 2001-2003.   \par \par \uc2 PT Internasional Nickel Indonesia's (INCO) President Director Arif Siregar said that the condition has been worse as there is no new contract signed in the last six years, as the term and condition on the contract is not attractive anymore for domestic as well as international mining company.   \par \par \uc2 "On the green field exploration \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Indonesia contributed 1.5% only. It shows that in the next 10-20 years,