\par\par \b \uc2 Council mulls release of reserve funds for monorail   \b0\par\par\uc2 The Jakarta Post , Jakarta   \par \uc2 375 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 August 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 4\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 The City Council is considering releasing Rp 250 billion (about US$27.4 million) in reserve funds to PT Jakarta Monorail (JM) to speed up the stalled construction of the monorail.   \par \par \uc2 The reserve funds, which total Rp 500 billion, come from money leftover from provincial budgets since 2000.   \par \par \uc2 "We are going to discuss it first with our political constituents," said councilor Sayogo Hendrosubroto, chief of commission D overseeing development affairs.   \par \par \uc2 He said the usage of reserve funds was allowed under a 2000 bylaw that stipulated that such funds could be used as emergency money for handling disasters, severe \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recessions or big projects the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  had an interest in.   \par \par \uc2 "The monorail project can be considered an urgent project to overcome the transportation problems faced by Jakartans," Sayogo said, adding that the council was still waiting for an official letter requesting use of the funds from Governor Sutiyoso.   \par \par \uc2 "We can use the funds if the proposal request follows the existing bylaws," Sayogo said.   \par \par \uc2 He added that the existing contract would have to be amended as the monorail project is currently supported entirely by private investors.   \par \par \uc2 "In the contract, it is stated that the administration will only give support to the project in the form of issuing technical policies and permission, which will sustain the project, but if the situation is like this, then the agreement between the Jakarta administration and JM must be changed," said Sayogo, although he did not detail what changes would be made.   \par \par \uc2 The $650 million monorail project has suffered financial problems for some times, with several investors backing out of earlier deals.   \par \par \uc2 State officials have argued over giving financial guarantees to secure overseas loans, with Finance Minister Sri Mulani Indrawati refusing to issue a blanket guarantee until the project complies with existing regulations.   \par \par \uc2 By law, the central government can only issue a risk guarantee for an infrastructure project if the developers were selected through a transparent tender.   \par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the project's financing and the irregular pace of construction work caused Sutiyoso to announce earlier this year that the city would break its contract with JM if the company could not make the construction completion deadline of 2007.   \par \par \uc2 (09)   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060815e28f0000e\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2 Natural Disaster  \highlight22\uc2 Regulation \highlight\uc2  Draft Needs Insurance Clause  \b0\par\par\uc2 462 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 August 2006\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 Bisnis Indonesia  \par \par \uc2 JAKARTA: Members of parliaments have different opinions on whether it is necessary to put the clause of insurance on the Natural Disaster \b \highlight22\uc2 Regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  Draft.  \par \par \uc2 The Parliament's Chairman of Commission VII Agusman Effendi agreed that insurance clause should be incorporated into the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 "It is a good way out, but I will let the special committee to incorporate it or not. But I have opinion in mind that it is a good solution," he said when Bisnis Indonesia called him presently.  \par \par \uc2 Ramson Siagian, a member of Commission VII, has a different perspective. He said that insurance is unnecessary as the government has the obligation to cover the loss. The compensation, he said, should consider the ability of state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .  \par \par \uc2 He said that insurance is not something obligatory for the citizen, but it is optional.  \par \par \uc2 "The government will have to redevelop the infrastructure at the aftermath of natural disaster. The citizens can take part, but it is not compulsory."  \par \par \uc2 Ramso also said that the per capita incomes of Indonesian citizens are various so that it will create \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  on the involvement to the insurance program. "If insurance clause is included into the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it will become something compulsory."  \par \par \uc2 In the meantime the Chairman of Indonesian General Insurance Association (AAUI) Frans Sahusilawane said that insurance is something important to reduce the government's burden in handling the impact of natural disaster.  \par \par \uc2 If it insurance clause is incorporated into the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the private sector will be able to take part in the burden.  \par \par \uc2 "So far the financing is only from state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and international support. The problem is that we have to change the system from the unplanned to the well planned one. If it is well planned, we can calculate how much the government's burden, and how much the people's share, through insurance."  \par \par \uc2 When asked whether insurance will increase the cost he said that high cost is unavoidable. But it will be able to reduce the government's burden.  \par \par \uc2 Burden sharing  \par \par \uc2 Frans said that if the clause is incorporated into the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2 , it could be determined further on how the government and the private sector will share the burden. "That is why we need a legal umbrella. The \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be promulgated at the first place."  \par \par \uc2 Kornelius Simandjuntak, PT Asuransi Himalaya Pelindung's President Director, said that insurance is serious aspect on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery process. "It is necessary to incorporate the clause on insurance, especially the compulsory property insurance," he said.  \par \par \uc2 He said that the compulsory insurance plan will reduce the government's burden in recovering the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  facility as well as in recovering the business activities.  \par \par \uc2 The insurance coverage, partly or totally, will ease the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  burden in redeveloping their properties. (Bisnis/asa)  \par \par \uc2 Document BISNIS0020060816e28g0000j\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
