\par\par \b \uc2 A conservative  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\b0\par\par\uc2 Politicians may consider President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono's state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal for 2007 a boring document, devoid of bold \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  measures and without any frills at all.   \par \uc2 708 \uc2 words\par \uc2 18 August 2006\par \uc2 The Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par 6\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 2006 The Jakarta Post   \par \par \uc2 But it is precisely the conservative assumptions used in the planned \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  that will reassure the market that there are unlikely to be any painful amendments midway through the next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year.   \par \par \uc2 As a communication system for providing signals about \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  behavior, prices, priorities, intentions and commitments, the 2007 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan reflects adequate \b \highlight22\uc2 public expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  management.   \par \par \uc2 It will focus \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on sectors directly related to human resource development, the improvement of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  service delivery, physical infrastructure as well as good governance through an increase in the salaries of civil servants and members of the armed forces. The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  also will continue \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  consolidation by cutting the \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  to 0.9 percent of gross domestic product.   \par \par \uc2 The assumptions on key sectors such as an average rupiah exchange rate of Rp 9,300, an oil price of US$65 a barrel, inflation at 6.5 percent and a benchmark short-term interest rate of 8.5 percent are realistic enough to allow for good \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  management.   \par \par \uc2 These assumptions are strikingly different from the 2006 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal which had to be revised extensively before it was finally approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  in late October, 2005.   \par \par \uc2 The 24 percent increase envisaged in income \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  receipts is not too optimistic if it is set against the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth target of 6.3 percent but on the condition that the taxpayer base should be broadened significantly.   \par \par \uc2 On the other hand, the 8 percent decline projected in non-\b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenues should be welcomed as this means that state companies will no longer be squeezed to allocate a greater portion of their profits for dividend pay out. This \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will thus allow them to reinvest a good portion of their earnings for future growth.   \par \par \uc2 The proposed increase of only 8 percent in total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 746.5 trillion (US$80 billion) is conservative enough to signal that the total amount of money the government will spend will be closely aligned to what is affordable over the 2007 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year.   \par \par \uc2 The central government will account for more than 66 percent of the planned total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  and regional administrations for the remainder. But the real significance of the central government's \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  will not be as high as the nominal sum indicates because more than half of that amount will be spent on debt servicing and fuel and electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Even though total government debt ratio against gross domestic product has fallen sharply to 41 percent this year, the rigors of debt will still be a big burden on next year's \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Domestic and foreign debt servicing (including amortization) will account for almost 19 percent of total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . No wonder, the official capital account will still suffer a net resource outflow next year. But this burdensome payment will further reduce the government debt ratio to a mere 37 percent later next year, making the debt burden much more sustainable and reducing the country's sovereign risks.   \par \par \uc2 The government wisely decided to avoid the risk of further turbulence of inflationary pressure and instead opted to increase fuel and electricity \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  to Rp 109.7 trillion or almost 15 percent of the planned total \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 .   \par \par \uc2 Even though the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  allocates Rp 138 trillion for the procurement of services and goods, including capital goods, the overall impact of the 2007 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will still be contractive on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  because of the stepped up \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -collection effort and bigger \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  on \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  and debt servicing.   \par \par \uc2 Hence, private investment and exports should expand significantly to become the locomotive of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. New investment will most likely run at a much higher pace because the high degree of predictability provided by the more realistic \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan will allow for efficient and effective implementation of policies and programs.   \par \par \uc2 A \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  system, however capable, is not self-contained, it does not operate in a vacuum, as it will be adversely affected by multiple, converging \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , entrenched patterns of \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2 , inflation and structural imbalances between expectations and resources.   \par \par \uc2 The proposed 2007 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  seems to be designed to cope with these realities.   \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020060818e28i0000h\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
