par \par \uc2 On Nov. 1-3, the government will hold the Infrastructure Conference and Exhibition 2006 with the aim of attracting investors to put their money into its infrastructure projects.  \par \par \uc2 Assuming that the government succeeds in attracting investors, ADB principal economist Ramesh Subramaniam said that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth could average 7 percent between 2006-2009.  \par \par \uc2 "This is an exciting time for us because the government has decided to increase development \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Of the $4 billion in loans, around $1 billion would be allocated to support the government's infrastructure program," Greenwood said.  \par \par \uc2 An ADB report shows that its active Indonesia portfolio in 2006 saw total new loans of $2.7 billion for 37 projects. This compared with over $1.6 billion for 32 projects that failed to be disbursed between 2003 and 2005.  \par \par \uc2 "The situation regarding undisbursed loans has actually improved dramatically in the last four to five years here in Indonesia in terms of ADB involvement," Greenwood said.  \par \par \uc2 "The $1.6 billion, I don't think it's a bad number. Keep in mind that as we approve loans, the projects usually take 6 to 7 years to actually accomplish."  \par \par \uc2 When asked about the growing skepticism in some quarters on the efficiency of international financial institutions, such as the ADB, Greenwood said the ADB was not concerned about improving its image, but rather would focus on delivering more effective programs.  \par \par \uc2 "Less about improving our image and more about doing the right thing for Indonesian," he said.  \par \par \uc2 If taken up by Indonesia, the loans would have an eight-year grace period and carry a 32-year maturity profile.  \par \par \uc2 Apart from providing loans, the ADB extended some $300 million in grants for Aceh and Nias after the tsunami disaster, and another $10 million for the victims of the recent Central Java and Yogyakarta earthquake.  \par \par \uc2 Document JKPOST0020061101e2b100008\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
