ht to be appointed and must be welcomed," the Vice President said.  \par \par \uc2 Irwandi Yusuf and Muhammad Nazar are former members of GAM (Free Aceh Movement) which had been fighting for an independent Aceh state since 1976.  \par \par \uc2 After decades of living in \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  and insecure conditions as a consequence of the armed conflict between GAM and governemnt security forces which ended with the Helsinki peace accord of August 15, 2005, the regioaal chief elections mark the beginning of a new era for the Acehnese people.  \par \par \uc2 More than 2 million voters had flocked to polling stations all over the province to elect a governor, district heads and mayors on Monday.  \par \par \uc2 The eight pairs of gubernatorial candidates which contested Monday's elections were Malik Raden-Sayed Fuad Zakaria, Humam Hamid-Hasbi Abdullah, Azwar Abubakar-M. Nasir Djamil, Iskandar Hoesin-Saleh Manaf, Tamlicha Ali-Harmen Nuriqmar, Djali Yusuf-Syaukas Rahmatillah, Irwandi Yusuf-Muhammad Nazar and Ghazai Abbas-Salahuddin Al Fatarh.  \par \par \uc2 Document ANTARA0020061213e2cc0000a\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
